This paper is about sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of neural methods for sentiment analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.AI and cs.LG). Additionally, the paper introduces a new dataset for sentiment analysis, which could be relevant to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SD).
